04:35.487 --> 04:39.514
Philip, look at my hair.
I can't go out like this.

04:39.825 --> 04:41.622
I gotta go to the salon.

04:41.693 --> 04:43.251
Well, you went yesterday, sweetheart...

04:43.328 --> 04:45.626
that's why we couldn't
have lunch together.

04:45.730 --> 04:46.924
Right, you're right.

04:47.098 --> 04:49.157
Henri tried something new, do you like it?

04:51.069 --> 04:53.094
Will, what do you think?

04:53.805 --> 04:54.794
Will!

04:57.375 --> 04:59.605
Well, actually, Aunt Viv, you got a...

04:59.811 --> 05:02.302
kind of a Don King...

05:04.583 --> 05:09.577
Kris Kross, Bride of Frankenthing going.

05:10.222 --> 05:11.849
Not many people could pull it off.

05:11.923 --> 05:16.553
Y ou know, as you're proving, right, but...

05:17.963 --> 05:19.021
What, Carlton?

05:19.731 --> 05:22.461
Vivian, where were you yesterday?

05:23.735 --> 05:25.703
Shooting baskets with Michael Jordon.

05:31.343 --> 05:33.903
Y ou know,
Clair would never talk to Cliff like that.

05:38.750 --> 05:40.149
What, Carlton?

05:50.362 --> 05:53.854
Y o, my brother, when the going
gets tough, the tough gets going.

05:54.399 --> 05:56.026
It's Hammer time.

05:59.371 --> 06:01.703
Sorry about that, man, you know,
you have to excuse my cousin...

06:01.773 --> 06:04.003
you know, he's an idiot.

06:06.912 --> 06:09.073
Carlton, can you please relax, man?

06:09.147 --> 06:12.548
Okay, I won't say another word.
I won't even make eye contact.

06:13.718 --> 06:15.310
Oh, God, what a stallion.

06:16.788 --> 06:18.449
Time to saddle up.

06:21.026 --> 06:22.015
Y o, what's up, baby?

06:22.093 --> 06:24.561
Hurry up, write your number down
before I don't want it no more.

06:28.400 --> 06:30.493
I'm sorry. How are you doing?

06:30.568 --> 06:33.230
I'm Will and this is my cousin, Carlton.

06:33.305 --> 06:34.465
Hi, I'm Simone.

06:34.539 --> 06:37.372
Thanks for coming down.
I'm going to show you what to do.

06:37.442 --> 06:39.273
And I'm going to buy you a car.

06:41.079 --> 06:42.137
No, thanks.

06:42.213 --> 06:44.374
But I do need a strong pair of arms.

06:44.449 --> 06:46.440
That would be me. I got that.

06:46.785 --> 06:50.312
Carlton can't help you,
he's on the debate team.

06:52.324 --> 06:55.054
Really, I'm captain of my debate team.

06:59.064 --> 07:01.692
Simone, where you want me
to go with this?

07:02.300 --> 07:05.633
How about over there somewhere,
like, say, Cleveland?

07:08.039 --> 07:11.133
Tell me to go to Cleveland,
mushroom head.

07:15.480 --> 07:17.971
Well, I guess we better get busy.

07:18.049 --> 07:19.414
All right!

07:21.519 --> 07:22.884
Oh, right.

07:35.300 --> 07:38.531
Listen, Simone, why don't you
come by the school on Monday...

07:38.603 --> 07:40.264
we're debating <i>Roe v. Wade.</i>

07:40.505 --> 07:42.336
Oh, reproductive rights!

07:42.741 --> 07:45.539
No, row versus wade,
the best way to cross a stream.

07:51.282 --> 07:53.011
Y ou've got a great sense of humor.

07:53.084 --> 07:54.483
Y eah, I know.

08:00.759 --> 08:03.751
- What's the matter?
- It's just a splinter.

08:04.829 --> 08:07.263
Better let me take a look
at that finger for you.

08:29.854 --> 08:32.186
- Damn!
- Problem, sir?

08:32.624 --> 08:35.616
It's Vivian.
I don't know what's gotten into her.

08:36.061 --> 08:37.961
This morning she told me
that I've become too...

08:38.029 --> 08:40.861
- Predictable, sir?
- Y es, that's exactly what she said.

08:41.131 --> 08:44.465
- She said that I wear the same...
- Blue shirt every weekend, sir?

08:44.536 --> 08:47.835
Y es, I mean, just because a man has...

08:47.906 --> 08:49.430
Froot Loops every morning.

08:49.507 --> 08:52.032
- Just because I watch...
- <i>Lega/ Beag/es</i> every night.

08:52.110 --> 08:53.873
Does that mean
that I've become predictable?

08:53.945 --> 08:56.413
Absolutely not, sir.

08:56.614 --> 08:59.708
Why, you're a regular
hotbed of spontaneity.

09:00.618 --> 09:02.415
- Y ou're welcome.
- Thank you.

09:14.399 --> 09:16.924
Hilary, why doesn't anyone want my soda?

09:17.001 --> 09:19.595
Because your soda's flat.

09:24.642 --> 09:27.406
Do you believe this mess, man?
I thought we was here to work.

09:27.479 --> 09:30.880
Don't even sweat it, man. Most of those
fools ain't coming back here, anyway.

09:30.949 --> 09:33.281
A few more months, everybody's
conscience will be cleared...

09:33.351 --> 09:35.182
and things will be back to status quo.

09:36.020 --> 09:39.456
Half these people don't even understand
what really went down here, man.

09:39.757 --> 09:40.746
Y eah.

09:41.793 --> 09:43.886
- Hey, I'm Noah, man.
- Hey, what's up? Will.

09:45.430 --> 09:47.455
And then when I was 12, I played Maria...

09:47.532 --> 09:49.727
in an all-boy production
of <i>West Side Story.</i>

09:56.941 --> 09:58.636
Carlton, slow down.

09:58.743 --> 10:00.938
I want to hear more
about your collection of Sea-Monkeys.

10:02.647 --> 10:04.308
Will you marry me?

10:08.219 --> 10:10.414
Well, there go the nerdyweds.

10:15.593 --> 10:18.892
Vivian, wait.
Now, you cannot avoid me all day.

10:19.097 --> 10:20.758
Now, where were you yesterday?

10:20.832 --> 10:24.495
Philip, I love you sweetheart.
Trust me, you're my husband.

10:24.569 --> 10:26.833
And, as your husband,
I have a right to an explanation.

10:26.905 --> 10:28.566
And, as your wife...

10:28.840 --> 10:31.070
when I think of something,
you'll be the first one to know.

10:31.142 --> 10:32.939
Don't... I'm not finished
with you yet, woman.

10:33.011 --> 10:34.842
Well, I'm through with you, man.

10:36.347 --> 10:37.939
Y eah, that's right, I'm bad.

10:55.266 --> 10:58.702
Man, I'm beat.
Got blisters on top of blisters.

10:58.770 --> 10:59.964
Y eah, me, too.

11:00.038 --> 11:01.733
Hey, so what time
you coming back tomorrow?

11:01.806 --> 11:04.900
I can't make it tomorrow, man.
I got school and everything, you know.

11:04.976 --> 11:08.434
Oh, yeah. Well, I'll get with you
next weekend, then.

11:08.880 --> 11:11.280
Oh, man. Well, I can't make it
next weekend, you know...

11:11.349 --> 11:14.580
I got a date on Saturday
and then I got a ball game on Sunday.

11:14.652 --> 11:17.951
- So, you know how it is, man.
- Y eah, I know how it is.

11:18.423 --> 11:20.323
Y ou're not coming back.

11:23.828 --> 11:26.262
Wait, hold up, man, I'm coming back.

11:26.431 --> 11:28.194
No, you're not, man.

11:28.566 --> 11:31.126
I bet you feel pretty good
about yourself, don't you?

11:31.202 --> 11:33.432
I mean, you come down here,
do the right thing...

11:33.504 --> 11:37.372
then you go home patting yourself on the
back 'cause you helped out the poor folk.

11:38.343 --> 11:42.143
Hold up, man. Y o, I'm from Philly.
We had to save up to be poor.

11:46.718 --> 11:48.811
Why you sweating me like this man,
what's up?

11:48.886 --> 11:51.116
'Cause, you're just like all the rest of them.

11:51.189 --> 11:53.919
Y ou come around here with the X cap
and them cool Doc Martens...

11:53.992 --> 11:55.823
and you're all "dope"
and "word to your mother."

11:55.893 --> 11:57.383
And you think that makes you committed?

11:58.863 --> 12:00.888
Let me tell you something,
this ain't no game.

12:00.999 --> 12:03.058
And if you think that it is,
then maybe you should go home...

12:03.134 --> 12:04.692
'cause you're not welcome here.

12:05.970 --> 12:07.961
Tell Dan Quayle I said, "What's up."

12:15.513 --> 12:17.242
Now I'm not welcome here, right?

12:17.315 --> 12:19.340
Well, you got your story
a little wrong, homey.

12:19.417 --> 12:21.078
This community appreciates me.

12:22.687 --> 12:24.211
I don't even know Dan Quayle.

12:27.859 --> 12:30.054
Hey, I'm going to
knock your head off, slimeball.

12:30.561 --> 12:31.619
Y o, man!

12:37.435 --> 12:39.266
Help!

12:40.805 --> 12:41.863
Shut up, bad man.

12:41.939 --> 12:43.531
Put your hands up and
put down the toaster.

12:43.608 --> 12:45.974
Put your hands up in the air,
put down the toaster.

12:46.044 --> 12:48.478
Make up your mind, man.
What do you want me to do first?

12:48.579 --> 12:50.945
Will! What the hell is going on in here?

12:52.417 --> 12:55.716
Dad, don't do anything stupid,
you haven't updated your will yet.

12:58.589 --> 13:00.784
Oh, my God. Hector?

13:01.292 --> 13:02.884
Y eah, what? Wait...

13:04.362 --> 13:06.387
Wait a minute, I know you.

13:06.464 --> 13:08.864
Y eah, ain't you
the guy from <i>Fami/y Matters?</i>

13:09.701 --> 13:13.899
- Y es!
- No, I'm Philip. Philip Banks.

13:14.372 --> 13:15.396
- Curly?
- Y eah.

13:15.940 --> 13:16.929
Oh, my God!

13:19.811 --> 13:22.006
Curly? They must go way back.

13:22.747 --> 13:26.808
Vivian, come here quick.
Oh, my God, what's it been, years?

13:29.287 --> 13:32.484
Oh, I don't believe it. It's Hector Alvarez.

13:34.092 --> 13:35.992
Oh, kids, look it's Hector.

13:36.761 --> 13:37.750
Hector!

13:38.596 --> 13:40.120
How are you?

13:41.165 --> 13:43.759
- Y ou look wonderful.
- So do you.

13:44.369 --> 13:46.132
- Who's Hector?
- I don't know, but be nice to him...

13:46.204 --> 13:47.228
